Cross-Border M&A Tracker - Q2 2025
Providing insights into the latest trends and dynamics shaping the global mergers and acquisitions landscape in Q2 2025.
Top 10 Inbound Deals
Takeover of RST Retail by E-commerce Behemoth
Leading e-commerce company acquires RST Retail, a prominent brick-and-mortar retail
chain, to accelerate its omnichannel strategy and expand its physical footprint.
Acquisition of VWX Media by Global Media Conglomerate
Multinational media conglomerate acquires VWX Media, a diversified media company with
strong content creation and distribution capabilities, to bolster its global media and
entertainment portfolio.
Merger of YZA Fintech and BCD Bank
Leading fintech company and a major regional bank combine to create a financial services
powerhouse offering integrated digital banking and financial technology solutions.
Takeover of LMN Aerospace by Aerospace Giant
Global aerospace and defense firm acquires LMN Aerospace, a prominent aircraft parts
manufacturer, to strengthen its supply chain and enhance its manufacturing capabilities.
Acquisition of OPQ Healthcare by Multinational Pharma
Multinational pharmaceutical company acquires OPQ Healthcare, a leading provider of
medical devices and digital health solutions, to expand its portfolio of innovative healthcare
products and services.
Acquisition of ABC Corporation
Global tech conglomerate acquires leading software company ABC Corp for $2.5 billion to
expand its cloud computing capabilities.
Merger of XYZ Industries and PQR Inc.
Two major manufacturing firms in the automotive sector combine to create a global
manufacturing powerhouse with a presence in 20 countries.
Takeover of GHI Pharma by Multinational Biotech
Multinational biotech firm acquires GHI Pharma, a leading specialty pharmaceutical
company, for $1.8 billion to bolster its pipeline of innovative drug treatments.
Acquisition of JKL Logistics by Logistics Giant
Global logistics conglomerate acquires JKL Logistics, a prominent freight forwarding and
supply chain management company, to strengthen its international logistics network.
Merger of MNO Energy and PQR Power
Two major energy companies in the renewable energy sector combine to create a global
leader in wind and solar power generation with a presence across 15 countries.

Legal and Tax Trends
Cross-Border Regulatory Compliance
Navigating the legal and regulatory landscapes across
different jurisdictions to ensure compliance with laws and
regulations
Tax Optimization Strategies
Exploring tax-efficient structures and incentives to
minimize the tax burden for cross-border M&A
transactions
Due Diligence Best Practices
Conducting comprehensive due diligence to identify and
mitigate legal, financial, and operational risks associated
with cross-border deals
Cross-Border Dispute Resolution
Establishing effective mechanisms for resolving disputes
and addressing post-merger integration challenges
across different legal systems
Intellectual Property Protections
Ensuring the appropriate protection and transfer of
intellectual property assets in cross-border M&A
transactions
5
Sectoral Insights
Technology
The technology sector continues to be a
hotspot for cross-border M&A, driven by rapid
digital transformation, AI/ML advancements,
and the growing demand for cloud-based
solutions.
Healthcare
The healthcare industry witnessed significant
M&A activity as companies sought to expand
their global footprint, access new markets, and
capitalize on emerging trends like telemedicine
and personalized medicine.
Renewable Energy
Renewable energy companies were highly
sought-after acquisition targets as the global
shift towards sustainability and clean
technologies accelerates, with investors
looking to diversify their portfolios.
Consumer Goods
The consumer goods industry experienced notable M&A activity as
companies sought to acquire innovative brands, gain access to new
distribution channels, and capitalize on evolving consumer preferences.
Financial Services
The financial services sector saw a surge in cross-border M&A as firms
aimed to enhance their digital capabilities, expand their customer base, and
adapt to the changing regulatory landscape.

Flags and Risks for Future Deals
Geopolitical Tensions
Potential impact of political and economic
instability, trade wars, and other global events on
cross-border deals
Integration Complexities
Difficulties in effectively integrating operations,
systems, and workforce across different countries
and regions
Regulatory Hurdles
Changes in government policies, trade regulations,
and cross-border compliance requirements that
can impact deal approvals and timelines
Cultural Differences
Challenges in aligning corporate cultures,
communication styles, and decision-making
processes across organizations
Intellectual Property Risks
Concerns around the protection and transfer of
intellectual property assets during the M&A
process

The Q2 2025 Cross-Border M&A Tracker provides valuable
insights into the latest trends and dynamics shaping the global
mergers and acquisitions landscape. By understanding the key
deal flows, legal and tax considerations, and sectoral patterns,
organizations can better navigate the complexities of cross-
border M&A and identify potential opportunities and risks for
future transactions.
